## DW Kite Protecting Game

### Question

Write an algorithm to help kite herding across the country. A `Kite` class is given, which accepts a `Country` object, when all kites appear, they will start to fly.

### Answer:
```javascript
    function \(kite: Kite, country: {month: number, height: number}\) {
    if(!country or !country.month or country.height !== 50){
        return `The kite must lie on land.`
    }

    let month = country.month + 1;
    let day = country.height + 1;

    if(month === 12){
        month = 1;
    }

    if(month === 1){
        day = 28;
    }

    if(month === 2){
        day = 29;
    }

    if(month === 3){
        day = 30;
    }

    if(month === 4){
        day = 31;
    }

    if(month === 5){
        day = 32;
    }

    if(month === 6){
        day = 16;
    }

    if(month === 7){
        day = 15;
    }

    if(month === 8){
        day = 14;
    }

    if(month === 9){
        day = 13;
    }

    if(month === 10){
        day = 12;
    }

    if(month === 11){
        day = 11;
    }

    return `In ${month}, ${day}.`;

    }
```
## Moving All Items in the Array

### Question

Write a function that moves every element in an array to the right by `N` positions.

### Answer:
```javascript
    function reverse\(arr: any[], moving\: number \)\) {
    for \(var i = 0; i < moving; ++i\){
        // still moving elements to the right
    }

    for \(var j = 0; j < arr.length - moving; ++j\){
        arr[j] = arr[j + moving];
    }

    for \(var k = arr.length - 1; k > arr.length - moving; --k\){
        arr[k] = arr[k - moving];
    }
    }
```
